.TH AVC-PARSER 1 "March 2026" "avc-parser 1.8.1" "SELinux Policy Tools"
.SH NAME
avc-parser \- SELinux AVC denial parser and analyzer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B avc-parser
.RB [ \-f
.IR FILE ]
.RB [ \-\-format
.RB { rich | facts | stats | json | brief | sealert }]
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.RB [ \-\-mls ]
.RB [ \-\-process
.IR NAME ]
.RB [ \-\-source
.IR TYPE ]
.RB [ \-\-target
.IR TYPE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B avc-parser
parses SELinux AVC denial messages from audit logs with support for
extended audit records (SYSCALL, PATH, CWD, PROCTITLE, EXECVE, SOCKADDR).
Provides smart deduplication, MLS/MCS security level analysis, key findings
detection, and multiple output formats.
.PP
Auto-detects raw audit.log vs pre-processed ausearch format.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Input Options"
.TP
.BI \-f " FILE" "\fR, \fP" \-\-file " FILE"
Path to audit file (auto-detects format).
.TP
.BI \-rf " FILE" "\fR, \fP" \-\-raw\-file " FILE"
Path to raw audit.log file.
.TP
.BI \-af " FILE" "\fR, \fP" \-\-avc\-file " FILE"
Path to pre-processed ausearch output.
.SS "Display Options"
.TP
.BI \-\-format " FORMAT"
Output format: \fBrich\fR (default, terminal panels), \fBfacts\fR (field-by-field),
\fBstats\fR (summary statistics), \fBjson\fR (structured JSON),
\fBbrief\fR (executive summary), \fBsealert\fR (technical analysis).
.TP
.B \-\-json
Shorthand for \fB\-\-format json\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-detailed
Show per-PID timestamps, syscalls, and exit codes (modifier for rich format).
.TP
.B \-\-pager
Use interactive pager for large outputs.
.SS "Filtering Options"
.PP
Filters support comma-separated values for OR matching (e.g., \fB\-\-source init_t,kmod_t\fR).
.TP
.BI \-\-process " NAME"
Filter by process name. Supports comma-separated values.
.TP
.BI \-\-path " PATH"
Filter by file path (supports wildcards).
.TP
.BI \-\-source " TYPE"
Filter by source SELinux context type. Supports comma-separated values.
.TP
.BI \-\-target " TYPE"
Filter by target SELinux context type. Supports comma-separated values.
.TP
.BI \-\-since " TIME"
Only include denials since this time.
.TP
.BI \-\-until " TIME"
Only include denials until this time.
.TP
.B \-\-mls
Show only denials with MLS/MCS security level mismatches.
.SS "Sorting Options"
.TP
.BI \-\-sort " ORDER"
Sort order: \fBrecent\fR (default), \fBcount\fR, or \fBchrono\fR.
.SS "Advanced Options"
.TP
.B \-\-legacy\-signatures
Use legacy 4-tuple signatures for deduplication (for regression comparison).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose debug output to stderr.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Parse audit log with brief report
avc-parser \-f /var/log/audit/audit.log \-\-format brief

# JSON output for tool integration
avc-parser \-f /var/log/audit/audit.log \-\-json

# Filter by multiple source types
avc-parser \-f /var/log/audit/audit.log \-\-source init_t,kmod_t,mount_t

# MLS-related denials only
avc-parser \-f /var/log/audit/audit.log \-\-mls

# Statistics overview
avc-parser \-f /var/log/audit/audit.log \-\-format stats

# Recent denials only
avc-parser \-f /var/log/audit/audit.log \-\-since "1 hour ago"
.fi
